The body of a 27-year-old man was found floating in a river in Centane, Eastern Cape, on Sunday. Police spokesperson Capt Jackson Manatha said Zwelethu Njama was reported missing on Saturday. A search was launched, but police were unable to track him, Manatha said. A passerby discovered his body floating in a river in Nxaxo village on Sunday at around 7am. Manatha said he had no visible injuries and his cellphone was found with him.